t/dateheader_02.gif"><span CLASS="newsdate">Mon 04 Dec 2006</span></TD><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_03.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE><br><!-------Start News item--><table cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="94%" border=0>             <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_01.jpg"></td>           <td  width=100%        background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_02.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_03.jpg"></td></tr>         <tr>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_04.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td>           <td             background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_05.jpg"><a name="23998"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Little Brown Pony?</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/100307561">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=23998>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=23998">Mail News</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">It seems that the players are a <a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=332060&view=by_date_ascending&page=2">little disappointed</a> that the legendary steed, "Ghostrider," whose bridle drops in Deathknell, is a small brown horse.  They feel he should be a much more impressive mount, not a "draft pony."<br><br>Developer Prathun, who designed the encounter where the legendary steed's bridle drops, had this to say:<br><br>"...it sounds like the perception is that the item is named first and then we apply stats based on the name.  This couldn't be further from the truth.  Zajeer created the bridle (and all the other drops in Deathknell) and submitted them to me for naming.  I named it Ghostrider... not because the horse was white, or a pegasus, or really cool, or a motorcycle ridden by a guy in a leather jacket that has a flaming skull for a head, but because it's a musical reference to "Ghost Riders in the Sky".  If you look at the list of drops in the zone you'll notice that nearly all of them are musical references of one sort or another, which should make sense considering that Deathknell is the God of Music's last holdout against the corruption of Mayong.<br><br>Now that I've got the origin cleared up, onto the meat of the issue.  Is the Ghostrider model unique?  Yes.  The horse is unique in that it's the only fast tan-hued horse in EverQuest.  Would it be cooler if we created a unique model with horns and flames and an oversized spoiler specifically for Ghostrider?  Sure.  Is that going to happen?  Not likely."<br><br>So, if you see somene with a tan horse that can go really fast, that's Ghostrider.  He's just like the famous racehorse Seabiscuit -- not so much to look at, but wicked fast!<br></span><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Mon 04 Dec 2006</span><br><br><br><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/spacer.gif" width="540px" height=1></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_06.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td></tr>         <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_07.jpg"></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_08.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_09.jpg"></td></tr></table></p><!-------End News item--><p><TABLE WIDTH="94%" BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0><TR><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_01.gif"></TD><TD WIDTH="100%" background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_02.gif"><span CLASS="newsdate">Fri 01 Dec 2006</span></TD><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_03.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE><br><!-------Start News item--><table cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="94%" border=0>             <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_01.jpg"></td>           <td  width=100%        background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_02.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_03.jpg"></td></tr>         <tr>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_04.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td>           <td             background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_05.jpg"><a name="23935"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">DevChat Logs November 29</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/100274012">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=23935>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=23935">Mail News</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">If you missed the Stratics House of Commons developer chat on Wedensday, they have posted <a href="http://eq.stratics.com/content/hoclogs/20061129.php">the logs</a> on their site.<br><br>The devs discuss the Serpent's Spine, the Progression server, itemization, tradeskills, and more.  One of the more interesting from quotes from Rashere involves some future game features:<br><br>"We have several zone revamps in the pipeline right now, the first of which will be coming out with the patch next week. In addition, there are a bevy of holiday events heading your way and the new year will bring some surprising changes to the world of Norrath, but you'll have to wait and see for those."<br><br>Sounds intriguing!<br></span><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Fri 01 Dec 2006</span><br><br><br><a name="23934"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Nanyea Interviews Dev Nodyin</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/100273957">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=23934>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=23934">Mail News</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">Nanyea has posted a short <a href=http://eq.crgaming.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=11320">interview</a> on Caster's Realm with David "Nodyin" Ford about his new position as alternate advancement designer.</span><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Fri 01 Dec 2006</span><br><br><br><a name="23933"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Comic Creator Contest from SOE</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/100273929">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=23933>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=23933">Mail News</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">Think you can write funny comics?  Comic Creator software is so easy to use (you can see my comics right here on EQVault using the program), anyone with some creativity can make awesome comics!<br><br>SOE is having a <a href="http://www.station.sony.com/contests/index.vm">contest</a> from Friday, December 8th 2006 (12:01 am, PST) through Friday, January 5th, 2007 at (11:59 pm, PST) with a prize of $250 for the best holiday comic:<br><br>"Create a Winter/holiday-themed comic book using the SOE Comic Book Creator software! Comics must be relevant to one or more of the following games: EverQuest, EverQuest II, and/or PlanetSide."<br><br>You can even get a free trial version of the software from SOE.</span><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Fri 01 Dec 2006</span><br><br><br><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/spacer.gif" width="540px" height=1></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_06.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td></tr>         <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_07.jpg"></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_08.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_09.jpg"></td></tr></table></p><!-------End News item--><p><TABLE WIDTH="94%" BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0><TR><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_01.gif"></TD><TD WIDTH="100%" background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_02.gif"><span CLASS="newsdate">Thu 30 Nov 2006</span></TD><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_03.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE><br><!-------Start News item--><table cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="94%" border=0>             <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_01.jpg"></td>           <td  width=100%        background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_02.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_03.jpg"></td></tr>         <tr>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_04.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td>           <td             background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_05.jpg"><a name="23878"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Host Your Website with Us!</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/100247959">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=23878>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=23878">Mail News</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">Do you have a great EverQues